Kgosi Mampuru prison in Pretoria .AFP Photo/Stefan Heunis PRETORIA - A manhunt is underway for two prisoners who escaped from the Kgosi Mampuru II Correctional Centre in Pretoria. One of the escapees is serving a life sentence for rape, robbery and kidnapping. The other is said to be serving 20 years for house-breaking crimes. NEED: Kgosi Mampuru C-Max section renovated Correctional Services is investigating how they managed to escape. More details to follow.